            <h1>SOUTH KOREA</h1>
            <p>South Korea, or the Republic of Korea, is located in East Asia. South Korea is very popular in terms of urban lifestyle. It is a developed country with a highly educated and skilled workforce.</p>
            <p>Wondering what is the special of South Korea? And what is some popular stuffs among South Korea? You can find the answer here. </p>
            <p>There is a phenomenom called the Korean Wve, which is known for its trendy and fashionable style. This is including K-Pop (Korean Pop) and K-Drama (Korean-Drama), which become popular among the asian.</p>
            
            <h2>Tourism</h2>
                  
                <h3>Seoul</h3>
                <p> Seoul is the capital city of South Korea. It is a modern city that lives up to the '24-hour party' tag. There are a lot of exciting places to go for eat, drink, shop, and relax.</p>
                <p> In Seoul, you can go visit Gyeongbokgung Palace and watch the Royal Guard Changing Ceremony every hour between 10 a.m. to 4 p.m., or you can try and experience lots of delicious street food. Some people recommend that you have to try at least Tteokbokki (we call it spicy rice cakes), or Kimbap (seaweed rice rolls).</p>
                
                <h3>Jeju Island</h3>
                <p>Jeju Island is located 85km off the coast of South Korea. It has a unique history, traditional dress, architecture and linguistic traditions. On the island, there are some places that really interesting such as botanical gardens, lava caves, sandy beaches, a folk village, and the O'Sulloc Tea Museum where you can study and lear about South Korea's famous traditional tea.</p>
                <p>Here are another places that you could go that is located in Jeju Island : Seongsan Ilchulbong Peak, Cheonjiyeon Falls, and Hallasan Mountain</p>
                
                <h3>Gwang-An Bridge</h3>
                <p>Gwang-An Bride, or sometimes they call it as the Diamond Brdige, is a bridge that connects Haeundae-gu and Suyeong-gu. You can also see the view of sandy beaches, hills, city lights, and mountain from it.</p>
                
                <h2>Interesting Facts:</h2>  
                <ul>
                    <li>In South Korea, babies are considered as one year old at birth.</li>
                    <li>South Korea is one of the lowest percentage in the world in terms of overweight. There are only 3.2 percents of South Koreans who are overweight.</li>
                    <li>When people write their Korean's name in red ink, it means that the person is going to die or is already dead.</li>
                    <li>Men in South Korea are love to do make up!</li>
                </ul>
                
          
            <h2>FOOD</h2>
            <p>As we know that South Korea has traditional dishes that make you couldn't stop eating! Here are some popular dishes from South Korea:  </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Hangover Stew (Haejangguk)</li>
                    <p>Hangover stew is a very popular dish in South Korea. It comes in a piping hot earthenware dish. You can eat it with porkspine bones, with rich, spicy, and flavored with tender chunks and Korean chilli paste.</p>
                    
                    <li>Chili Pickled Cabbage (Kimchi)</li>
                    <p>Who does not know Kimchi?! This is one of the foods that is very popular in South Korea! Kimchi is an appetizers. There are so many types of Kimchi, the most popular one is a kimchi made from napa cabbage</p>
                    
                    <li>Soft Tofu Stew (Sundubu Jjigae)</li>
                    <p>Soft Tofu Stew is a flavorful Korean dish with a flaming hot pot of Sundubu Jjigae. It is made with some seafood, tofu, plus an egg on top.</p>
                </ul>
          
